The article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Donald J. Trump on June 4, 2018. The memorandum is titled "Suspension of Limitations under the Jerusalem Embassy Act" and is related to foreign policy. In the memorandum, President Trump invokes his authority as President to suspend for a period of 6 months the limitations set forth in sections 3(b) and 7(b) of the Jerusalem Embassy Act of 1995. He determines that this suspension is necessary to protect the national security interests of the United States. The memorandum directs the Secretary of State to transmit this determination and a report to Congress, as required by the Act, and to publish the determination in the Federal Register. The suspension will take effect after the transmission of the determination and report to Congress.